        "committer": {
          "name": "Niu Yawei",
          "email": "yawei.niu@intel.com",
          "date": "2013-09-11 03:02:57.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "LU-3884 lu: use proper flag for lu_object_put_nocache()",
        "message": "LU-3884 lu: use proper flag for lu_object_put_nocache()\n\nlu_object_put_nocache() was using dying flag\n(LU_OBJECT_HEARD_BANSHEE) to indicate that the caller doesn't\nwant to cache current object, however, this introduces a\nproblem: if lu_object_put_nocache() is called for an object\nwhich is holding by somebody else, the object will be marked\nas dying but kept in cache until it released by the holder.\n\nThis patch introduced nocache flag (LU_OBJECT_NO_CACHE) for\nlu_object_put_nocache(). The dying flag should only be used\nfor the object that is really dying soon.\n\nSigned-off-by: Niu Yawei <yawei.niu@intel.com>\nChange-Id: If82eb821b749c0c6d168992349fa79343d222bfc\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
